1. Lesotho was formerly known as Basutoland, and is now officially the
Kingdom of Lesotho.
2. Lesotho is home to the Sani Pass - one of the most dangerous mountain
passes in the world by vehicle due to its many hairpin turns.
3. This is a landlocked country, meaning it has no direct connection
to nearby seas or oceans.
4. Lesotho is not only a landlocked country, but it is completely surrounded
on all sides by South Africa, making it one of the few enclave countries
in the world.
